.TH TODOLET 1 "July 2026" "todolet 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
todolet \- week-at-a-glance to-do list for the terminal
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B todolet
.br
.B todolet add
.I TEXT
.RI [ DAY ]
.br
.B todolet list
.RI [ OFFSET ]
.br
.B todolet export
.RI [ FILE ]
.br
.B todolet import
.I FILE
.br
.B todolet ical
.RI [ OFFSET | FILE ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B todolet
is a terminal companion to the todolet.app web app: see the week ahead, add
tasks to a day, tick them off. No accounts, no cloud, no dependencies \(em one
Python file and a JSON file on your own machine.
.PP
Run with no arguments to open the interactive TUI. Press
.B ?
inside the TUI for the key reference.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI add " TEXT " [ DAY ]
Quick-add a task.
.I DAY
may be
.BR today ,
.BR tomorrow ,
a weekday name
.RB ( mon .. sun ),
.BI + N
days from today, or a
.B YYYY-MM-DD
date. Defaults to today.
.TP
.BI list " " [ OFFSET ]
Print a week to stdout.
.I OFFSET
is in weeks:
.BR 0 ", " +1 ", " \-2 ", ..."
.TP
.BI export " " [ FILE ]
Write a backup JSON in the todolet.app backup format.
.TP
.BI import " FILE"
Merge a backup JSON (accepts web-app backups). Tasks are merged by id and
duplicates are skipped; nothing is deleted.
.TP
.BI ical " " [ OFFSET | FILE ]
Export a week as an iCal
.B .ics
file.
.TP
.B help
Show usage.
.TP
.B version
Show the version.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/todolet/todolet.json
Task storage, in the same shape as the web app's localStorage, so backups
move freely between phone and terminal in both directions.
.SH SEE ALSO
.UR https://todolet.app
.UE
.SH AUTHOR
Chris Naylor
